MaxValue is the highest value that can be set
Weight is a mulptlier

Text:
To transform your data into a graph using Mermaid.js Live Editor's `graph TD` syntax, you'll need to represent each entity, attribute, relation, goal, condition, and decision variable as nodes. Below is an example of how you can structure this graph:

```mermaid
graph TD

    %% Entities in blue
    subgraph "Entities"
        E1([Entity1]):::entity
        E2([Entity2]):::entity
        E3([Entity3]):::entity
    end
    
    %% Attributes in white, around entities
    A1([Attribute1]):::attribute --> E1
    A2([Attribute2]):::attribute --> E1
    A3([Attribute3]):::attribute --> E2
    A4([Attribute4]):::attribute --> E3
    
    %% Relations in orange between entities
    R1([Relation1]):::relation -->|connects| E1 & E2
    R2([Relation2]):::relation -->|connects| E2 & E3
    
    %% Goals in green connected to entities/attributes
    G1([Goal1]):::goal --> E1
    G2([Goal2]):::goal --> A4
    
    %% Conditions in red connected to entities/attributes
    C1([Condition1]):::condition --> E2
    C2([Condition2]):::condition --> A3
    
    %% Decision Variables in purple connected to relevant entities
    DV1([DecisionVariable1]):::decision --> E1
    DV2([DecisionVariable2]):::decision --> E3

%% Styles
classDef entity fill:#blue,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
classDef attribute fill:#white,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
classDef relation fill:#orange,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
classDef goal fill:#green,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
classDef condition fill:#red,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
classDef decision fill:#purple,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
```

### Explanation:

- **Entities**: Represented as blue nodes.
- **Attributes**: Connected to their respective entities and colored white.
- **Relations**: Orange lines connecting entities they relate.
- **Goals**: Green nodes connected to entities or attributes they pertain to.
- **Conditions**: Red nodes linked to specific entities or attributes.
- **Decision Variables**: Purple nodes associated with relevant entities.

### Customization:

Replace `Entity1`, `Attribute1`, etc., with your actual data. You can add more nodes and connections as needed by following the same pattern. This structure allows you to visualize complex relationships in a clear, color-coded manner using Mermaid.js.
